name: Auraria Library
description: The Auraria Library is located in downtown Denver, and serves the students, faculty, and staff of three leading urban institutions. We strive to create a welcoming environment that fosters equity, diversity, and inclusion.

name: 1015 - 9th Street Park
description: CU Denver English Department Building. The Knight House was built in 1885 by Charles and Betsey Davis. It is considered one of the most perfectly proportioned Victorian houses in Denver.

name: 1020 - 9th Street Park
description: Shared Building - Casa Mayan. One of the oldest two houses on the block, built circa 1872 by William Smedley. Later became one of the city's first Hispanic operated Mexican restaurants.

name: 1024 - 9th Street Park
description: MSUD ROTC Building. Built in 1875, this graceful villa was the home of Oscar and Cordelia Room until 1903. Features roofline iron cresting.

name: 1027 - 9th Street Park
description: AHEC Marketing Office. The towered and crested With House was built circa 1883. Spacious rooms and the decorative tower make this a favorite of visitors.

name: 1033 - 9th Street Park
description: MSUD Honors Building. Built in 1873 by carpenter Jeremiah Gardner in the stick style. One of only two frame structures in the block.

name: 1041 - 9th Street Park
description: Shared Building - Faculty Club. Probably built circa 1880, this brick bay front is a variance on the Italianate style.

name: 1045 - 9th Street Park
description: MSUD OWOW. Built in 1890 for William Schultz. The only double on the block.

name: 1047 - 9th Street Park
description: CU Denver UHL. Built in 1890 for William Schultz. The only double on the block.

name: 1050 - 9th Street Park
description: CU Denver English Department Building. Charming brick one-story cottage built circa 1875. Possibly the oldest brick residence left standing in the community.

name: 1051 - 9th Street Park
description: CU Denver English Department. Built in 1903 by Thomas Young. Typical classic cottage style with central dormer window.

name: 1056 - 9th Street Park
description: AHEC Planning Department Offices. A classic cottage characterized by its hip roof and central dormer window.

name: 1059 - 9th Street Park
description: CU Denver English Department. Built in 1880, this mansard structure has impressive architectural credentials. Remodeled by Frank Edbrooke.

name: 1061 - 9th Street Park
description: English Dept. Probably built around 1874. Simplest of the Italianate on Ninth Street.

name: 1068 - 9th Street Park
description: AHEC Executive Team Offices. Italianate villa built by miller Charles R. Davis circa 1873. One of the two oldest residences on the block.

name: Los Molinos
description: The one commercial structure on the block, built in 1906. Now serves as the Auraria Campus restaurant Los Molinos.

name: Emmanuel Gallery
description: Since 1973, The Emmanuel Art Gallery exhibits the work of exceptional artists from around the world and Colorado.

name: Golda Meir House
description: The Golda Meir House Museum on the Auraria Campus is her only known U.S. residence. It celebrates a theme inspired by Golda's life.

name: St. Cajetan's Center
description: Built in 1926 as a church for Spanish-speaking Roman Catholics. Now serves as a multi-purpose auditorium.

name: St. Elizabeth's Church
description: A vibrant urban faith community located on the Auraria Higher Education Campus.

name: King Center
description: A modern performing arts complex with over 180,000 square feet dedicated to education and development in performing arts.

name: Lola & Rob Salazar Student Wellness Center
description: Features three levels of unique and flexible spaces including gym courts, spa, and study rooms.

name: 5th Street Garage
description: Campus Parking Garage.

name: 5th Street Hub
description: Home to the College of Engineering, Design and Computing machine shop and Capstone Design projects.

name: 7th Street Garage
description: Parking and Transportation Services. Parking lots are open to students, faculty and campus visitors.

name: Arts Building
description: Home to the College of Arts & Media. Features classrooms, recording studios, and the Department of Visual Arts.

name: Auraria Early Learning Center
description: Provides exceptional care and education for children. 5-star Colorado Shines-rated center.

name: Business School
description: Hub of innovation, collaboration and discovery. Largest accredited graduate school of business in the Rocky Mountain region.

name: CU Denver Building
description: Home to the College of Architecture and Planning. Contains 3-D digital animation labs.

name: Lawrence Street Center
description: Home to the School of Public Affairs, Graduate School, and School of Education & Human Development.

name: North Classroom
description: One of the largest buildings on campus. Home to College of Engineering, Psychology, and more.

name: PE/Event Center
description: Home of Campus Recreation at Auraria and the Outdoor Recreation Center.

name: Plaza Building
description: Houses the Health Center at Auraria and Dept of Modern Languages.

name: Science Building
description: Houses state-of-the-art labs and classrooms for Anthropology, Math, Biology, and Chemistry.

name: Student Commons
description: Devoted solely to students' education and success. Contains most student service operations.

name: Student Success Building
description: Student Success Building.

name: Tivoli Parking Garage
description: Parking Garage for Tivoli.

name: Tivoli Student Union
description: Built in 1866 as a brewery. Now serves as the student union.

name: West Classroom
description: West Classroom Building.

name: City Heights Residence Hall / Learning Commons
description: Affordable housing option that doubles as a central hub for academic enrichment. Known as City Heights / Learning Commons.

name: Lynx Crossing
description: Furnished apartment-style units including a full kitchen or kitchenette in every unit.
